  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large tava or griddle over medium heat.",
    "Add the diced potato and cook until slightly tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the smoked haddock fillets and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side, until flaked and cooked through.",
    "Add the fermented kimchi, chopped parsley, salt, and black pepper to the tava, stirring to combine with the haddock and potatoes.",
    "Squeeze the lemon juice over the top and stir to combine.",
    "Cook for an additional 2-3 minutes, until the mixture is heated through and the flavors have melded together.",
    "Serve the smoked haddock hash hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired.",
    "Garnish with additional lemon wedges if desired."
